properties.journal_entry: Nearly Calm all day am Carpenter on board the I bark Teekalet of New York In the Mediterranean Lea. Lat 39°.14 North. Long 1° 13 East. bound to Leghorn Italy with tobacco
The wind Easterly fresh breeze and overcast at 4 oclock in the afternooon reefed fore and main topsail tacked ship of the Island  Corsica wind increasing
The wind Easterly sair breeze set all sail. for the afternoon reefed Main topgallant sail. at 4 PM. tacked ship of the Island of Corsica
Nearly Calm all day and very pleasant. of the island of Corsica at night very moderate to the West. Shacpeled chain on Port bow anchor
The wind Westerly. in ther morning and within 20 miles of Leg horn. at 8.AM took the wind very moderate to the East
The wind Easterly anchored in Leghorn at 8 oclock in the forenoon. and moored head and stern Reed two letters from home and wrote one home
The wind Easterly and rainy in morning discharged of tobacco. afternoon the wind Northerly and pleasant Got finger jamed in cojes of winch. went to Hospital got it done up
The wind Easterly and very pleasant.
The wind Easterly discharged in three lighters with tobacco. in forenoon. Went to Hospital and had finder done up
The wind East discharged in two lighter with tobacco
The wind Easterly wrote letter to J.H.S. and Galen Smith. Went to Hospital and got fingers done up
The wind Easterly Went to Hospital had finger done up very severe pain
Made an other visit to the Doctors for the cure of my finger Exceedingly painful
A visit to the Doctor
Went to the Hospital to to stay until the cure of my finger
The pain Exceedingly great
Had finger lanced to the bone from middle point to End after the Doctors had held long consultation
Finger so badly inflamed the doctor dare not take it of
Finger and hand very badly inflamed. cloths wet in ice water laid on back of my hand to stop the inflamation from going up any higher.
Was removed in an arm chair up several flights of stairs to the upper part of the building. A long consultation of Doctors as to whether it was best to take my finger off
No inflamation in hand but for some reason un noon to me, the doctors have decided not to trouble my hand to day
In Hospital at Leghorn so much run down by exceedingly great pain I am unable to get of my bed not having strength to stand alone
In Hospital at Leghorn
In Hospital at Leghorn Italy
Belong to the Bark Tukalet of New York but have been put ashore in the Hospital on account of a lame hand and expect to have it taken of

NA
Wrote letter home from the Hospital

Had finger taken of below the point founel the bone to  be unsonnd and then it was unjointed
NA

Commence to gain strength so I can walk about the hospital
Still in the hospital waiting patiently to be able to get back on board the Bark

Left the Hospital and went on board the vessel
Calm all day. went to the Hospital and had hand dressed
The wind Easterly Took pilar on board and Sailed from Leghorn for New York Sent letter shore by pilot for home at dark calm
The wind East fresh breeze run all day with studding sails set. Passed the Rock of Gibraltar about noon Clear weather
The wind W.N.W. Took in studding sails and stood to the Southward & Westward by the wind. Sail the Canary Islands to the Southward Lat 32°20 Long 13° 30
The wind Easterly and pleasant got underway and went to sea bound For Cape Haiti took departure from the Highland of Neversink

Calm all day and very hot. took down main rigging to refit it and put up new cross tries.
